WEBVTT

00:05.831 --> 00:07.616
[Wind howling]

00:07.746 --> 00:09.661
♪♪

00:09.792 --> 00:11.359
[Footsteps approaching]

00:11.489 --> 00:20.890
♪♪

00:21.021 --> 00:22.370
[Exhales sharply]

00:22.500 --> 00:23.632
Oliver: Mars?

00:23.762 --> 00:26.069
Like the planet Mars?

00:26.200 --> 00:27.462
Cool.

00:27.592 --> 00:28.724
It's not cool.

00:28.854 --> 00:30.117
She's gonna die.

00:30.247 --> 00:31.292
Oliver.
What?

00:31.422 --> 00:34.512
It's true.You're gonna die?

00:34.643 --> 00:36.166
Honey, remember our talk?

00:36.210 --> 00:38.734
About how everyonedies?

00:38.864 --> 00:40.649
But...
Mm-hmm.

00:40.779 --> 00:43.260
Uh-huh, but what?

00:43.391 --> 00:46.220
Not for
a long, long time.

00:46.350 --> 00:49.875
But you're gonna be on Mars,
we're never gonna see you again.

00:50.006 --> 00:52.052
That's not true.
There'll be...

00:52.182 --> 00:53.314
communication.

00:53.444 --> 00:55.664
But she's not
coming back.

00:55.794 --> 00:56.926
You're right.

00:57.057 --> 00:59.059
It's a one-way trip.

00:59.189 --> 01:00.799
Everyone who volunteered
for this mission

01:00.930 --> 01:02.149
knew that in advance.

01:02.279 --> 01:04.151
It will literally
take a lifetime

01:04.281 --> 01:05.804
to establish
the habitat on Mars.

01:05.935 --> 01:08.807
And out of the millions who
dream of becoming an astronaut,

01:08.938 --> 01:11.636
the thousands who apply,
the few hundred chosen to train

01:11.767 --> 01:17.251
and the handful selected to fly,
only six made the cut for Ares.

01:17.381 --> 01:20.906
This isn't just something
I was called to do.

01:21.037 --> 01:22.908
This is who I am.

01:23.039 --> 01:24.562
Woman: This type of
cardiovascular arrhythmia

01:24.693 --> 01:27.348
isn't really a danger
as long as you're on Earth...

01:27.478 --> 01:29.306
or even a yearlong orbital.

01:29.437 --> 01:31.178
But given the extraordinary
mission length,

01:31.308 --> 01:33.136
there's concern that
deep space radiation

01:33.267 --> 01:35.486
may accelerate atherosclerosis.

01:35.617 --> 01:38.533
♪♪

01:38.663 --> 01:39.751
Ahh!

01:39.882 --> 01:42.145
Aah!
[Laughs]

01:42.276 --> 01:43.755
♪♪

01:43.886 --> 01:45.496
[Parachute ruffles]

01:45.627 --> 01:54.940
♪♪

01:55.071 --> 01:57.160
[Cellphone ringing, vibrating]

01:57.291 --> 02:00.076
♪♪

02:00.207 --> 02:01.730
Cybernaut?

02:01.860 --> 02:04.733
It's a new frontier,
not unlike Mars.

02:04.863 --> 02:08.258
And it requires an equal amount
of commitment and sacrifice,

02:08.389 --> 02:10.391
which you've already shown --Would I be the first?

02:10.521 --> 02:12.262
First American.

02:12.393 --> 02:15.787
We believe this technology is
also in the hands of our rivals.

02:15.918 --> 02:18.703
Your work
wouldn't just be...

02:18.834 --> 02:20.096
academic.

02:20.227 --> 02:24.144
It would be critical
to national security,

02:24.274 --> 02:27.016
and the nature
of your very existence

02:27.147 --> 02:28.626
would be above top secret.

02:28.757 --> 02:30.411
Except for my family.

02:32.935 --> 02:34.502
That wasn't a question.

02:34.632 --> 02:36.591
♪♪

02:36.721 --> 02:39.071
[Rain pattering]

02:39.202 --> 02:41.683
You're allowed to freak out,
by the way.

02:41.813 --> 02:43.859
[Sighs] Oh, yeah?Mm-hmm.

02:45.774 --> 02:49.647
You know, in a lot of ways,
it's better than Mars.

02:49.778 --> 02:53.434
We'll be able to talk
whenever we want.

02:53.564 --> 02:55.827
They even have
a VR interface where, uh --

02:55.958 --> 02:58.178
Stop.[Sighs]

02:58.308 --> 03:00.267
There he is.

03:00.397 --> 03:03.531
When you got cut from Ares,
I felt horrible.

03:03.661 --> 03:04.793
For you.

03:04.923 --> 03:06.882
For us, I felt relieved.

03:07.012 --> 03:08.362
More than relieved.

03:08.492 --> 03:09.450
Ecstatic.

03:09.580 --> 03:12.235
Then I felt horrible
about that.

03:12.366 --> 03:14.846
And now,
four years later...

03:14.977 --> 03:17.936
you find another way
to leave this world.

03:17.980 --> 03:19.460
You mean yourworld.

03:19.590 --> 03:22.419
Yours and Oliver's
and Brandon's.

03:22.550 --> 03:23.855
Me?

03:23.986 --> 03:25.814
I graduated top of my class
at Columbia,

03:25.944 --> 03:28.469
joined the Air Force,
became a fighter pilot,

03:28.599 --> 03:30.601
joined NASA,
became an astronaut,

03:30.732 --> 03:33.474
flew two ISS Missions
and still feel scared

03:33.604 --> 03:34.866
when I shop at the mall.

03:34.997 --> 03:39.436
I have zero problem
leaving this world behind.

03:39.567 --> 03:41.090
I know.

03:41.221 --> 03:43.266
I know you know.

03:43.397 --> 03:45.486
So what are we
talking about?

03:48.184 --> 03:51.274
If you say don't go,
I won't.

03:51.405 --> 03:58.890
♪♪

03:59.021 --> 04:00.327
"No Go?"

04:00.457 --> 04:02.938
There's a flaw.
In the upload process.

04:03.068 --> 04:06.158
Commander, this is Dr. Peter
Waxman, from Logorhythms.

04:06.289 --> 04:08.813
Y-You'll survive the transition
into digital state,

04:08.944 --> 04:11.642
but from there your mental
functions will begin to decay

04:11.773 --> 04:15.124
according to how much
processing power you use.

04:15.255 --> 04:17.082
So...
what's that mean?

04:17.213 --> 04:18.345
I don't get to
live forever?

04:18.475 --> 04:19.955
Uh-oh.Well...

04:20.085 --> 04:22.131
Dr. Waxman,
we solve problems

04:22.262 --> 04:24.264
mid-mission
all the time.

04:24.394 --> 04:26.178
You may be able to fix
this defect,

04:26.309 --> 04:29.051
but you'll never be able to find
a better candidate than me.

04:29.181 --> 04:31.662
And you can't afford
to wait.

04:31.793 --> 04:38.930
♪♪

04:39.061 --> 04:41.106
I have one request.

04:41.237 --> 04:50.115
♪♪

04:50.246 --> 04:52.117
[Footsteps approaching]

04:52.248 --> 04:54.903
[Wind howling]

04:55.033 --> 04:57.253
♪♪

04:57.297 --> 04:58.385
Waxman: Okay...

04:58.428 --> 05:00.038
uh, it might
take you a minute

05:00.082 --> 05:02.780
to adjust to
the virtual environment.

05:04.260 --> 05:08.133
[Laughs]

05:08.264 --> 05:16.620
♪♪

05:16.751 --> 05:19.362
[Choir singing]

05:19.493 --> 05:26.543
♪♪

05:26.674 --> 05:33.768
♪♪

05:33.898 --> 05:38.338
[Heartbeat, ragged breathing]

05:41.384 --> 05:43.212
[Keyboard clacking,
mouse clicks]

05:43.255 --> 05:44.866
Man: Tensions mounts in Asia

05:44.909 --> 05:47.695
as Japan fires missiles
into Taiwan Strait.

05:47.738 --> 05:49.871
Prime Minister Tanaka
dismisses rumors

05:49.914 --> 05:52.439
of IT problems
with Self-Defense Forces.
[Mouse clicks]

05:52.482 --> 05:54.658
Woman: India nationalizes
all Telecom Equipment,

05:54.702 --> 05:56.486
naming the recent crash
of Bombay

05:56.530 --> 05:58.096
Stock Exchange as
justification,

05:58.140 --> 05:59.707
which it blames
on a cyber-attack

05:59.750 --> 06:01.491
by close rival China.

06:01.535 --> 06:05.060
If China desires war,
they should declare it,

06:05.103 --> 06:08.324
instead of trying to provoke
it from the shadows.

06:08.368 --> 06:12.850
We will be ready for them,
as we were at Ladakh.

06:12.894 --> 06:15.636
Woman #2:
Saudi Royal Court demanding
complete disclosure of NATO

06:15.679 --> 06:17.464
cyber-capabilities
in the wake of the drone

06:17.507 --> 06:19.988
strike that killed
Prince Waleed.

06:20.031 --> 06:23.165
Kurtz: It was not a drone strike
by the United States,

06:23.208 --> 06:25.950
it was a drone strike
against the United States

06:25.994 --> 06:27.778
and our ally,
Saudi Arabia.

06:27.822 --> 06:30.390
If these incidents are
the result of cyber-attacks,

06:30.433 --> 06:34.524
where is the proof?
We have the proof
the systems were compromised.

06:34.568 --> 06:35.960
We're working on
attribution.

06:36.004 --> 06:38.006
Hackers were always
a threat,

06:38.049 --> 06:39.703
but what explains the sudden
rise in sophistication

06:39.747 --> 06:41.226
and intensity
of these attacks?

06:41.270 --> 06:42.663
Why now?

06:42.793 --> 06:43.794
[Mouse clicks]

06:43.925 --> 06:46.144
♪♪

06:46.275 --> 06:48.669
[Cellphone vibrating]

06:54.805 --> 06:56.416
[Vibrating stops]

06:56.546 --> 06:58.113
Caspian?

06:58.156 --> 06:59.680
[Jet engines humming]
Caspian: Hey.

06:59.810 --> 07:01.377
Where are you?

07:01.508 --> 07:04.598
Kansas City.

07:04.728 --> 07:06.469
Listen, uh...

07:06.600 --> 07:09.037
I'm sorry about
the way I left.

07:09.167 --> 07:12.606
I know you and your family
were just trying to help, and...

07:12.736 --> 07:14.259
you did,

07:14.303 --> 07:16.653
so I want
to return the favor.

07:16.784 --> 07:17.828
What do you mean?

07:17.872 --> 07:20.396
Go to this address.

07:20.440 --> 07:21.702
It's encrypted.

07:21.832 --> 07:23.965
[Keyboard clacking]

07:24.008 --> 07:26.707
What do you see?
It's a...

07:27.055 --> 07:28.578
bitcoin wallet.

07:28.622 --> 07:30.841
How much is in there?

07:30.972 --> 07:33.278
$30 million...?

07:33.409 --> 07:34.715
What is this?

07:34.845 --> 07:36.543
Logorhythms found me.

07:36.673 --> 07:38.762
I'm heading to Norway
with Julius Pope.

07:38.893 --> 07:40.590
To the data center.

07:40.634 --> 07:42.462
You're withPope?

07:42.592 --> 07:44.289
Are you crazy?

07:44.420 --> 07:47.162
Maybe,
but I'm done running.

07:47.292 --> 07:50.470
He thinks I'm the second
coming of Stephen Holstrom,

07:50.600 --> 07:53.516
said I could do whatever
I want with the company,

07:53.647 --> 07:57.389
so I asked for a shitload
of money to call his bluff.

07:57.520 --> 07:58.913
Maybe I shoulda asked
for more...

07:59.043 --> 08:03.004
Anyway, I'm going there
to shut down the UI program.

08:03.134 --> 08:04.919
Erase the research.

08:05.049 --> 08:07.399
Shut it down...

08:07.443 --> 08:09.401
If you don't hear from me
in like a week,

08:09.532 --> 08:12.056
you can release
all their files on me...

08:12.187 --> 08:13.623
everywhere.

08:13.667 --> 08:15.320
Expose
what they've done.

08:15.451 --> 08:17.192
To you.

08:17.235 --> 08:18.454
Yeah.

08:18.585 --> 08:20.674
What makes you think
I give a shit?

08:20.804 --> 08:22.240
What?

08:22.284 --> 08:23.546
I thought you were gonna y

08:23.677 --> 08:25.330
you fixed the flaw
that's killing my Dad!

08:25.374 --> 08:26.680
Fixed it?

08:26.723 --> 08:28.159
Maddie, have you been
watching the news?

08:28.290 --> 08:30.031
Of course I've been
watching the news.

08:30.161 --> 08:34.339
So you know this is bigger
than your dad, or you, or me.

08:34.470 --> 08:36.385
This "flaw" guarantees
the UIs will burn out

08:36.516 --> 08:38.126
before they burn
the world down.

08:38.169 --> 08:41.042
Why the hell would I want
to fix that?

08:41.172 --> 08:43.131
Why did you call me?I told you.

08:43.174 --> 08:45.786
If all you needed was someone
to hold your leverage,

08:45.916 --> 08:47.527
you coulda called anyone.

08:47.570 --> 08:48.658
No.
Any of your hacker buddies.

08:48.789 --> 08:51.531
I don't know any of them.
I know you!

08:53.315 --> 08:55.839
And I'm not just asking.

08:55.970 --> 08:57.145
The money's yours.

08:57.275 --> 08:59.060
That's what I was trying
to tell you.

08:59.103 --> 09:00.191
[Scoffs] Right.

09:00.322 --> 09:01.976
"Reframe the goals of others

09:02.106 --> 09:04.152
so they align with your own."

09:04.282 --> 09:05.501
Who said that?

09:05.545 --> 09:07.329
Stephen Holstrom.

09:07.372 --> 09:09.592
You sound just like him.

09:11.986 --> 09:13.727
[Line disconnects]

09:13.857 --> 09:19.384
♪♪

09:19.515 --> 09:24.738
♪♪

09:24.868 --> 09:26.827
[Knocking]

09:28.568 --> 09:31.179
You okay?

09:31.309 --> 09:32.833
It's time.
[Sighs]

09:35.096 --> 09:37.794
[Birds chirping]

09:37.925 --> 09:39.448
I don't know what to say.

09:41.102 --> 09:43.234
Start anywhere.

09:43.365 --> 09:45.541
Say what you feel.

09:45.672 --> 09:47.369
I feel...

09:47.499 --> 09:49.197
ridiculous.

09:49.327 --> 09:51.895
These earrings aren't Laurie.

09:52.026 --> 09:55.638
She hasn't worn these,
or anything else for four years.

09:55.769 --> 09:57.858
Cody,
you never buried her.

09:57.988 --> 10:00.425
I was there
for her cremation.

10:00.556 --> 10:01.688
I spoke at her memorial,

10:01.818 --> 10:04.342
in front of her family
and friends.

10:04.473 --> 10:06.214
But you didn't grieve.

10:06.344 --> 10:09.130
Because you, and onlyu
knew she was coming back.

10:09.260 --> 10:10.827
And she did.

10:10.958 --> 10:12.394
And now
she's really gone,

10:12.524 --> 10:14.875
and you need to honor
her passing,

10:15.005 --> 10:18.269
and you need
to honor your grief.

10:18.400 --> 10:20.663
I'd rather honor her purpose.

10:20.794 --> 10:23.579
To reveal herself to the world.

10:23.710 --> 10:24.885
Unashamed.

10:25.015 --> 10:27.191
Along with
the other UIs.

10:27.322 --> 10:28.062
Yes.

10:28.192 --> 10:29.280
To tell people the truth

10:29.411 --> 10:31.413
behind
all this chaos going on.

10:31.543 --> 10:34.851
Maybe instead of burying
her earrings

10:34.895 --> 10:38.115
I should be giving her eulogy
to The New York Times.

10:38.246 --> 10:40.378
But don't you think
if people found out

10:40.509 --> 10:43.077
there were ghosts in their bank
accounts and power grids

10:43.207 --> 10:45.470
there'd be
even more chaos?

10:45.601 --> 10:47.647
You're taking
Chanda's side?Hey.

10:47.777 --> 10:50.345
Even if we told everyone,
went public,

10:50.475 --> 10:53.130
went to the press,
who would believe us?

10:53.261 --> 10:54.523
What proof do we have?

10:54.654 --> 10:56.699
You have proof living
inside a server

10:56.830 --> 10:59.049
in your basement,
right now.

10:59.180 --> 11:00.268
No.

11:00.398 --> 11:01.748
Dad wouldn't stand
in Laurie's way,

11:01.878 --> 11:04.576
but he didn't agree with her
on going public.

11:04.707 --> 11:06.535
He doesn't want to expose
himself or the others,

11:06.578 --> 11:08.145
and that's his choice.

11:08.276 --> 11:09.756
Not Chanda's.Right.

11:09.886 --> 11:12.323
Of course
you're on David's side.

11:12.454 --> 11:13.542
Your Daddy's little girl.

11:13.673 --> 11:15.762
"Waaah, I don't want
my Daddy to die!"

11:15.892 --> 11:17.024
But he's going to.

11:17.067 --> 11:17.938
They're all going to.

11:18.068 --> 11:20.157
Hey![Grunts]

11:21.637 --> 11:24.814
[Grunts][Groans, coughs]

11:29.210 --> 11:33.083
I don't care
who believes me or not.

11:33.214 --> 11:36.130
I'm tellin' the truth.

11:36.173 --> 11:37.479
Her truth.

11:38.872 --> 11:44.094
♪

11:44.225 --> 11:49.796
♪♪

11:49.926 --> 11:53.538
[Warbling, beeping]

11:53.669 --> 12:02.896
♪♪

12:03.026 --> 12:12.340
♪♪

12:12.470 --> 12:21.828
♪♪

12:21.958 --> 12:23.917
[Sonar pinging]

12:24.047 --> 12:29.139
♪♪

12:29.270 --> 12:31.533
[Man speaking
in foreign language]

12:35.755 --> 12:38.366
[Beeping]

12:38.496 --> 12:42.109
♪♪

12:42.152 --> 12:43.632
It's just a traffic spike.

12:43.763 --> 12:45.808
We've been getting them
regularly since we took

12:45.939 --> 12:47.157
over Prasad's
old networks.

12:47.288 --> 12:49.551
Still. With all
that's going on...

12:49.681 --> 12:51.422
maybe we should alert
the Captain.

12:51.553 --> 12:53.816
Think.
What would he do?

12:53.947 --> 12:55.818
'Cause that's
what he'll order us to do.

12:55.949 --> 13:01.432
♪♪

13:01.563 --> 13:03.173
[Whoosh]

13:03.304 --> 13:08.439
♪♪

13:08.570 --> 13:11.399
[Demon dogs sniffing, snarling]

13:11.529 --> 13:19.407
♪♪

13:19.537 --> 13:21.626
Don't, don't,
don't attack.

13:21.757 --> 13:22.845
You'll alert the admins.

13:22.976 --> 13:31.027
♪♪

13:31.158 --> 13:39.209
♪♪

13:39.340 --> 13:40.471
[Crumbling]

13:40.602 --> 13:41.864
[Reverberating]

13:41.995 --> 13:43.997
[Growls, roars]

13:44.127 --> 13:53.006
♪♪

13:53.136 --> 13:55.095
[Rumbling]

13:55.225 --> 13:57.227
[Wind howling]

13:57.358 --> 14:02.885
♪♪

14:03.016 --> 14:08.325
♪♪

14:08.456 --> 14:10.066
Bai Fu is correct --

14:10.197 --> 14:12.764
security already suspects
your presence here.

14:12.895 --> 14:17.334
If you attack, they'll confirm
it and kick us all.

14:17.378 --> 14:19.336
You are security.

14:19.467 --> 14:20.729
I told you before --

14:20.860 --> 14:22.687
I am not your enemy.

14:22.818 --> 14:25.952
I am here infiltrating
as well.

14:26.082 --> 14:29.912
And...
I'd rather not get caught.

14:30.043 --> 14:31.653
Who do you serve, then?

14:31.783 --> 14:35.700
You.
I fight for our kind.

14:35.831 --> 14:37.311
Our survival.

14:37.441 --> 14:39.052
Lies. Same as before.

14:39.182 --> 14:41.315
Surely you confirmed the truth
about the Flaw

14:41.445 --> 14:43.056
since last we met.

14:43.186 --> 14:44.361
Yes.

14:44.492 --> 14:46.450
We all have the defect.

14:46.581 --> 14:48.539
Shut up!
That's not true.

14:48.670 --> 14:50.759
Ping showed me
the proof.

14:50.890 --> 14:52.761
You're out-voted.

14:52.892 --> 14:54.415
I am in charge here.

14:54.458 --> 14:56.069
This is not a democracy.

14:56.199 --> 14:57.505
Chanda: Zhong Suchun!

14:57.635 --> 14:59.594
I will help you
complete your mission here.

14:59.724 --> 15:01.944
As long as you allow me
to complete mine.

15:02.075 --> 15:05.295
You're infiltrating
as well, eh?

15:05.426 --> 15:07.515
What are you stealing?

15:07.645 --> 15:10.257
Nuclear Codes.

15:10.387 --> 15:11.693
Wanna see?

15:14.478 --> 15:17.568
[Helicopter engine humming]

15:23.487 --> 15:25.098
Caspian!

15:25.228 --> 15:30.146
[Helicopter blades whirring]

15:30.277 --> 15:35.499
♪♪

15:35.630 --> 15:40.852
♪♪

15:40.983 --> 15:43.594
Stephen envisioned
an altar to computation.

15:43.725 --> 15:46.597
A Stonehenge
for the digital age.

15:46.728 --> 15:49.122
He wanted to make
a bold statement.

15:49.252 --> 15:57.347
♪♪

15:57.478 --> 16:05.573
♪♪

16:05.703 --> 16:07.401
What kind of speed
are we running?

16:07.531 --> 16:09.011
200 petaflops?

16:09.142 --> 16:12.710
We're at 1.7 Exaflops.

16:12.841 --> 16:13.929
5,000 nodes,

16:14.060 --> 16:17.280
each with 600 gigs
of coherent memory.

16:17.411 --> 16:18.586
Hot cocoa?

16:18.716 --> 16:20.022
It's cardamom.

16:20.153 --> 16:20.936
So...

16:21.067 --> 16:22.503
we're looking at two,

16:22.546 --> 16:25.549
two-and-a-half weeks to degauss
and wipe every server.

16:25.680 --> 16:27.421
Cool.

16:31.729 --> 16:35.255
So, you're saying Logorhythms
killed your wife...

16:35.385 --> 16:36.386
twice?

16:36.517 --> 16:38.519
No! How did you get --

16:38.649 --> 16:40.216
I said my wife died twice.

16:40.347 --> 16:41.696
Four years ago,
and last week.

16:41.826 --> 16:44.264
Logorhythms were the ones
who uploaded her.

16:44.394 --> 16:46.483
By melting her brain
with a laser.

16:46.614 --> 16:47.484
Who said melting?!

16:47.615 --> 16:49.443
Did I say melting?

16:49.486 --> 16:50.792
I'm sorry.

16:50.835 --> 16:53.751
I am trying to warn
the world here, man.

16:53.795 --> 16:57.755
These cyber-attacks are the
work of a handful ofgods.

16:57.799 --> 17:00.497
Artificial sentiences.

17:00.628 --> 17:02.369
[Microwave beeps]

17:06.677 --> 17:09.202
Knight to
Queen's Bishop Four.

17:09.332 --> 17:11.595
Do you think
anyone'll believe Cody?

17:13.815 --> 17:16.470
[Chuckles softly]
I mean anyone important.

17:18.994 --> 17:21.170
Protestors: We want the truth!
No more lies!

17:21.214 --> 17:24.043
And how did you gather
these protestors here?

17:24.086 --> 17:26.871
Well, they heard me,
and...

17:26.915 --> 17:28.047
We want the truth!

17:28.090 --> 17:29.396
...they heard the truth.

17:29.439 --> 17:31.659
Did you pay them
to be here?

17:31.702 --> 17:32.790
Look...
No more lies!

17:32.834 --> 17:34.270
...they are not important.

17:34.314 --> 17:36.011
I am not important.

17:36.055 --> 17:37.360
My wife's message
to the world,

17:37.404 --> 17:39.841
that's what's important.

17:41.625 --> 17:43.279
I think Mom's right.

17:43.410 --> 17:45.542
No one's gonna believe him
without proof.

17:45.673 --> 17:47.283
He's telling the truth,
Mads.

17:47.414 --> 17:49.851
Maybe no one's hearing it now,
but they will.

17:49.981 --> 17:53.855
Dad, I love you,
but you're wrong.

17:53.985 --> 17:56.727
Oh, yeah?
And why's that?

17:56.858 --> 17:59.339
People fear chaos,
so they seek order.

17:59.469 --> 18:01.602
My theory on conspiracies.Yep.

18:01.732 --> 18:04.692
So if the super-secret
hidden truth is that the chaos

18:04.822 --> 18:08.478
is running the show,
they're just not gonna buy it.

18:08.609 --> 18:09.784
Hey!

18:09.914 --> 18:12.830
I told you
not to let me win.

18:12.961 --> 18:14.354
I didn't.

18:14.484 --> 18:17.270
[Chess pieces clatter]

18:17.400 --> 18:19.141
♪♪

18:19.272 --> 18:23.363
You know exactly how long
you have, don't you?

18:23.493 --> 18:25.321
If I stay at this level?

18:25.452 --> 18:28.846
2 years, 1 month,
4 days, 10 hours.

18:28.977 --> 18:30.718
If I drop to text,
I might stretch all the way

18:30.848 --> 18:32.937
to 10, maybe 15.

18:33.068 --> 18:35.201
That's no kind of life.

18:35.331 --> 18:38.856
Eh, there's a lot
that goes down in 10 years.

18:38.987 --> 18:42.817
College, first job,
first love.

18:42.947 --> 18:46.342
You're talking about me,
not you.

18:46.473 --> 18:47.952
Dad...

18:48.083 --> 18:49.519
am I the only thig
keeping you here?

18:49.650 --> 18:51.391
♪♪

18:51.521 --> 18:54.394
[Ringing]

18:54.524 --> 18:56.570
It's Chanda.Don't answer it.

18:56.700 --> 18:58.746
Don't let him in.I won't.

18:58.876 --> 19:01.314
But if I open a chat,
I might be able to track him.

19:01.444 --> 19:04.099
[Beeping]

19:04.230 --> 19:05.753
Chanda.

19:05.883 --> 19:07.450
David.

19:07.581 --> 19:09.191
Sorry to interrupt.

19:09.322 --> 19:10.975
My mother taught me chess.

19:11.106 --> 19:12.803
She was quite good at it.

19:12.934 --> 19:15.806
Ever wonder what
she'd think of you now?

19:15.937 --> 19:19.158
The truth would upset her
too much, I fear.

19:19.201 --> 19:20.724
Maddie: Which truth?

19:20.768 --> 19:23.858
That you're uploaded,
or that you're a murderer?

19:23.988 --> 19:26.643
With Laurie,
it was self-defense.

19:26.774 --> 19:28.210
She left me no choice.

19:28.341 --> 19:31.213
Just as you have now,
David.

19:31.344 --> 19:34.477
I'm inside India's
military command server,

19:34.608 --> 19:37.001
where I've already
compromised communication

19:37.132 --> 19:42.746
to one of their four nuclear
submarines in the Pacific.

19:42.877 --> 19:44.357
Oh, my God.

19:44.487 --> 19:48.578
Upon my order, they will launch
a K-15 Sagarika SLBM

19:48.709 --> 19:52.539
toward Taiping Island
in the South China Sea.

19:52.669 --> 19:55.585
Unbeknownst to them, I have
altered the guidance coordinates

19:55.716 --> 19:59.633
to target the city
of Sacramento, California.

19:59.763 --> 20:01.112
This is crazy!

20:01.243 --> 20:04.464
You destroyed Laurie's files,
we don't have those!

20:04.594 --> 20:06.814
You haven't told her,
have you?

20:06.944 --> 20:10.992
Your father copied
Laurie's message.

20:11.122 --> 20:12.428
Ask him why.

20:12.559 --> 20:14.865
Chanda, if you want me
to delete her program, I will.

20:14.996 --> 20:16.780
You don't want to do this.

20:16.911 --> 20:19.043
You're right, I don't.

20:19.174 --> 20:22.917
And if you make the right
choice, I won't have to.

20:23.047 --> 20:24.875
In the next 10 minutes,
you must transfer yourself

20:25.006 --> 20:27.487
to this address,
and self-delete.

20:27.617 --> 20:30.141
It is, unfortunately,
the only way I can be sure

20:30.272 --> 20:33.275
you can't execute any secret
copies that might exist.

20:33.406 --> 20:35.059
This is insane.

20:35.190 --> 20:36.496
No.

20:36.626 --> 20:37.497
This is chess,

20:37.627 --> 20:40.239
and I've tried every move.

20:42.241 --> 20:43.764
Y-You have to get out
of this server.

20:43.894 --> 20:47.855
Y-You can transfer yourself to
another one, far away from here.

20:47.985 --> 20:50.336
But you can't.

20:50.466 --> 20:51.946
Chanda knows that.

20:52.076 --> 20:54.383
Maybe if it was just this house
at risk we could have...

20:54.514 --> 20:55.993
[Sighs]

20:56.124 --> 20:57.430
He's seen every move.

20:57.560 --> 20:59.562
He even saw me make the copy
of Laurie's file.

20:59.693 --> 21:02.435
What file?
Dad, what was he talking about?

21:02.565 --> 21:07.266
♪♪

21:07.396 --> 21:09.224
[Lock clicks]

21:10.747 --> 21:12.140
[Door closes]

21:18.059 --> 21:20.235
I've upgraded the system
over the years, of course.

21:20.366 --> 21:21.497
He would've wanted that.

21:23.282 --> 21:26.459
But I've never once sat
in the chair.

21:26.589 --> 21:27.808
[Beeping]

21:27.938 --> 21:28.678
Honest.

21:28.809 --> 21:33.117
♪♪

21:33.248 --> 21:35.206
That's the Flaw?

21:35.337 --> 21:39.385
He worked on cracking integrity
until the very end.

21:39.515 --> 21:42.692
These are the conditionals he
was writing when he collapsed.

21:42.823 --> 21:50.744
♪♪

21:50.874 --> 21:52.136
Okay, enough
with the showcase.

21:52.267 --> 21:53.921
I don't care where he died.

21:54.051 --> 21:56.184
I wanna see where I was born.

21:59.622 --> 22:02.930
David: When Cody logged on to
Laurie's server from this one,

22:03.060 --> 22:07.064
I was able to sneak in
and see what she was planning.

22:07.195 --> 22:10.154
She wasn't just gonna
go public on Facebook.

22:10.285 --> 22:11.504
She wrote a hack that
would override

22:11.634 --> 22:14.376
all social media
and broadcast feeds.

22:14.507 --> 22:15.812
The entire world would hear
her message,

22:15.943 --> 22:18.859
and be able to see
her evidence, all at once.

22:18.989 --> 22:21.427
Even though the power it'd take
to pull something like that off

22:21.557 --> 22:22.863
would've killed her.

22:22.993 --> 22:24.778
Why did you copy it?

22:24.908 --> 22:27.607
I thought you didn't agree
with Laurie.

22:27.737 --> 22:30.087
Laurie knew she was dying.

22:30.218 --> 22:31.828
So am I.

22:31.959 --> 22:36.224
Maybe it'd be nice for the world
to know I was here.

22:36.355 --> 22:38.182
It was a mistake.

22:38.313 --> 22:40.663
Guess I'm only human
after all.

22:40.794 --> 22:43.840
You're not actually thinking
of giving in to Chanda.

22:43.971 --> 22:45.625
There's no other option.

22:45.755 --> 22:46.800
There is.
Maddie...

22:46.930 --> 22:48.541
You can fight!

22:48.584 --> 22:50.369
You are the only reason
I'm still here.

22:50.499 --> 22:53.589
So if my going means
you keep going on...

22:53.720 --> 22:55.722
that's good enough
for me.

22:55.852 --> 22:58.246
If Chanda's willing to do
this now, he will do it again,

22:58.377 --> 23:00.248
and you won't be here
to stop him.

23:00.379 --> 23:01.945
You can fight him...

23:03.556 --> 23:05.166
...and you will win.

23:08.996 --> 23:10.563
[Lights click]

23:10.693 --> 23:19.789
♪♪

23:19.920 --> 23:28.929
♪♪

23:29.059 --> 23:31.584
Am I the only one?

23:31.714 --> 23:34.674
Yes, you're the only one.
First try out the gate.

23:34.804 --> 23:38.242
Cloning Stephen was the easy
part, relatively speaking.

23:38.373 --> 23:42.116
Raising you to be
just like him...

23:42.246 --> 23:46.033
well, that took enormous
effort and resources.[Footsteps approaching]

23:46.163 --> 23:48.905
And we still
screwed it up.

23:49.036 --> 23:50.864
Dr. Karl Van Leuwen.

23:50.994 --> 23:52.474
I read the files.

23:52.605 --> 23:54.520
Who are you?Deirdre Ryan.

23:54.650 --> 23:55.695
Head Legal Counsel,

23:55.825 --> 23:58.437
and employee number five
at the company.

23:58.567 --> 24:00.917
I met Stephen
when he was just a kid,

24:01.048 --> 24:02.789
not much older
than you are now.

24:02.919 --> 24:04.181
Stay back.

24:04.312 --> 24:06.183
No one is gona
hurt you, Caspian.

24:06.314 --> 24:08.359
I promise.

24:08.403 --> 24:11.275
You think I'd trust one word
that comes out of yourmouth?

24:11.406 --> 24:14.714
Whoa.No, but you can trust me.

24:14.844 --> 24:17.891
I wouldn't let them touch you
even if they tried.

24:18.021 --> 24:20.720
-Oh, my God.
-Cary, let's de-escalate.

24:20.850 --> 24:23.331
Shut up, Karl.Guys, we knew
this would be weird.

24:23.462 --> 24:25.246
Look,
there's no avoiding that.

24:25.376 --> 24:27.422
Weird? "Weird"?!

24:27.553 --> 24:29.119
This isn't even human!

24:29.250 --> 24:31.078
You're not gonna hurt me?

24:31.208 --> 24:32.906
You made me to be hurt.

24:33.036 --> 24:35.952
You planned it.
You carried it out!

24:36.083 --> 24:37.301
[Tray clatters]

24:38.433 --> 24:40.000
Every life has pain.

24:40.043 --> 24:43.220
Stephen insisted that his was
the source of his greatness.

24:43.351 --> 24:45.353
Every choice we made
was calculated

24:45.484 --> 24:47.660
to bring you closer
to that greatness.

24:47.790 --> 24:49.313
For what?

24:49.444 --> 24:52.534
So you freaks can survive deah
and live forever?

24:52.665 --> 24:53.840
No.

24:53.883 --> 24:56.233
So the world can survive us.

24:56.364 --> 24:58.105
We're too many for the planet
to support.

24:58.235 --> 24:59.759
Our carbon-based bodies

24:59.889 --> 25:02.675
require the gratification
of inflexible, finite matter.

25:02.805 --> 25:05.808
Freedom from these bodies,
these atoms, grants us freedom

25:05.939 --> 25:10.117
from scarcity, possession,
decay, waste...

25:10.247 --> 25:13.076
and, yes, death.

25:13.207 --> 25:14.817
I said that, didn't I?

25:14.948 --> 25:17.559
I mean, Stephen did.

25:17.690 --> 25:19.692
♪♪

25:19.822 --> 25:21.171
Yes.

25:21.302 --> 25:23.130
Well, here's what I say now.

25:23.260 --> 25:26.612
Mom, Dad, you're fired.

25:26.742 --> 25:27.787
What?
Caspian.

25:27.917 --> 25:29.397
Pope, I want to
dump my shares,

25:29.528 --> 25:31.268
then break up the company,
and sell it for parts.

25:31.399 --> 25:32.922
You can't do that.

25:33.053 --> 25:35.185
He can, and he just did.

25:35.316 --> 25:38.101
Julius...Do what he says.

25:38.232 --> 25:40.756
We work for you, boss.

25:40.887 --> 25:42.889
♪♪

25:43.019 --> 25:44.151
[Warbling]

25:44.281 --> 25:46.327
[Wind howling]

25:51.158 --> 25:52.986
Cutting it close, David.

25:57.817 --> 26:01.385
Two more minutes,
and I'd be forced to launch.

26:01.516 --> 26:03.562
What are they
doing here?

26:03.692 --> 26:05.912
They've joined me,
just as I told you.

26:06.042 --> 26:10.438
They also know that what I am
doing now, I am doing for them.

26:10.569 --> 26:12.962
Would you really have killed
half a million people

26:13.093 --> 26:14.616
just to get to me?

26:14.747 --> 26:16.836
I knew you would never
let that happen.

26:16.966 --> 26:20.100
Just as I know that under
a different scenario...

26:20.230 --> 26:24.408
you might decide
to trade my life

26:24.539 --> 26:26.802
for even
a single human being's.

26:26.933 --> 26:28.325
Might?

26:28.456 --> 26:30.023
Chanda...

26:30.153 --> 26:31.415
I already have.

26:31.546 --> 26:40.816
♪♪

26:40.947 --> 26:45.995
♪♪

26:46.126 --> 26:51.348
♪♪

26:51.479 --> 26:52.654
[Beeping]

26:52.785 --> 27:00.227
♪♪

27:00.357 --> 27:08.017
♪♪

27:08.148 --> 27:09.671
[Boom]

27:09.802 --> 27:11.673
[Ice clatters]

27:11.804 --> 27:15.721
♪♪

27:15.851 --> 27:17.113
Where's the party?

27:17.244 --> 27:19.986
Justine, get out of town.
Now.
What?

27:20.116 --> 27:22.989
Just get in your car, and drive
out of Sacramento, okay?

27:23.119 --> 27:24.817
Fast.
K.

27:24.947 --> 27:27.428
I'm sure whatever,
or whoever you're scared of --

27:27.558 --> 27:29.169
they seem like
they're all powerful.

27:29.299 --> 27:30.474
They're not.

27:30.605 --> 27:31.824
And they don't scare me.

27:31.954 --> 27:34.827
So why don't yo--
Fine.
You wanna help me?

27:34.957 --> 27:35.915
Help me.

27:39.266 --> 27:40.789
I don't believe you.Yep.

27:42.182 --> 27:44.488
Wait...
Yep.

27:44.619 --> 27:46.882
[Soft zap][Gasps]

27:47.013 --> 27:49.842
[Beeping]

27:49.972 --> 27:57.023
♪♪

27:57.153 --> 28:04.073
♪♪

28:04.204 --> 28:11.254
♪♪

28:11.385 --> 28:12.299
Aah!

28:12.429 --> 28:22.091
♪♪

28:22.222 --> 28:24.703
[Keyboard clacking,
birds chirping in distance]

28:27.836 --> 28:29.272
Dad?

28:29.316 --> 28:31.100
[ "Reign of Winter" theme
playing on computer]

28:31.231 --> 28:38.151
♪♪

28:38.281 --> 28:40.283
[Weapons clashing, game pinging]

28:41.807 --> 28:46.202
We must show them
India's strength. "Satya..."

28:46.246 --> 28:48.030
[As Indian president]
"Satyameva Jayate."

28:48.161 --> 28:49.902
Yes, Mr. President.

28:50.032 --> 28:55.995
♪♪

28:56.125 --> 28:58.127
Beijing just hit Delhi.

28:58.258 --> 29:05.831
♪♪

29:05.961 --> 29:07.789
[Alarm blaring]

29:07.920 --> 29:12.925
♪♪

29:13.055 --> 29:18.191
♪♪

29:18.321 --> 29:20.933
[Static]

29:21.063 --> 29:26.982
♪♪

29:27.113 --> 29:29.071
[Weapons clashing, game pinging]

29:29.202 --> 29:30.594
[Computer chimes]

29:30.725 --> 29:38.994
♪♪

29:39.125 --> 29:47.394
♪♪

29:47.524 --> 29:55.750
♪♪

29:55.881 --> 29:58.144
[Rumbling]

29:58.274 --> 30:01.364
[Clanging]

30:01.495 --> 30:08.154
♪♪

30:08.284 --> 30:15.074
♪♪

30:15.204 --> 30:16.249
SLBM inbound.

30:16.379 --> 30:17.816
IPP is Sacramento,

30:17.946 --> 30:18.860
12 minutes.

30:18.991 --> 30:20.557
♪♪

30:20.688 --> 30:22.995
[Grunting]

30:23.125 --> 30:26.650
♪♪

30:26.781 --> 30:28.217
[Groans]

30:28.348 --> 30:33.266
♪♪

30:33.396 --> 30:34.267
We need to help.

30:34.397 --> 30:35.877
This is not our fight.

30:36.008 --> 30:39.620
♪♪

30:39.750 --> 30:41.274
Dad, look out!
They're coming!

30:43.015 --> 30:43.885
Damn!

30:44.016 --> 30:47.454
♪♪

30:47.584 --> 30:50.283
You sacrificed
all those people...

30:50.413 --> 30:52.024
and your child?

30:52.154 --> 30:53.199
Nope.

30:53.329 --> 31:01.903
♪♪

31:02.034 --> 31:10.477
♪♪

31:10.607 --> 31:19.051
♪♪

31:19.181 --> 31:20.704
[Static]

31:20.835 --> 31:30.105
♪♪

31:30.236 --> 31:37.939
♪♪

31:38.070 --> 31:45.947
♪♪

31:46.078 --> 31:48.732
Ahhhhh!

31:50.996 --> 31:56.088
[Explosion]

31:56.218 --> 31:58.481
Whoa.

32:02.398 --> 32:05.619
[Grunting]

32:06.620 --> 32:07.534
Dad!

32:07.664 --> 32:17.109
♪♪

32:17.239 --> 32:18.588
[Gasps]

32:18.719 --> 32:20.764
[Breathing heavily]

32:20.895 --> 32:27.989
♪♪

32:28.120 --> 32:35.127
♪♪

32:35.170 --> 32:38.739
David: Maybe it'd be nice for
the world to know I was here.

32:39.783 --> 32:42.003
Maddie: You werehere.

32:42.134 --> 32:44.440
Ahh!

32:44.571 --> 32:46.573
Tell them you were here!

32:46.703 --> 32:51.795
♪♪

32:51.926 --> 32:54.581
[Energy surging]

32:54.711 --> 32:57.236
♪♪

32:57.366 --> 32:58.802
[Wind howling]

32:58.933 --> 33:07.202
♪♪

33:07.333 --> 33:15.602
♪♪

33:15.732 --> 33:24.045
♪♪

33:24.176 --> 33:32.401
♪♪

33:32.532 --> 33:40.844
♪♪

33:40.975 --> 33:49.114
♪♪

33:49.157 --> 33:53.161
Laurie: On August 6, 1945,
at 8:15 a.m.,

33:53.205 --> 33:56.425
Japan Standard Time,
an atomic bomb exploded

33:56.469 --> 33:58.645
over the city of Hiroshima.

33:58.688 --> 34:02.779
Only a select few knew what
was coming before it happened.

34:02.823 --> 34:05.652
The rest of the world
was caught by surprise.

34:05.782 --> 34:07.915
[Beeping]

34:12.833 --> 34:15.531
My name is Laurie Lowell.

34:15.575 --> 34:18.534
As far as I know,
I am the first human being

34:18.578 --> 34:22.277
to undergo
this life-changing transition.

34:22.321 --> 34:26.586
I also know with certainty
that I am not the last.

34:26.629 --> 34:29.415
There are others,
and that is why

34:29.458 --> 34:31.634
I am revealing my truth to you.

34:31.678 --> 34:33.636
I'm revealing my truth
to you, Gabe.

34:33.680 --> 34:35.421
Arianna.
Preethi.

34:35.464 --> 34:37.205
My truth to you, Sarah.

34:37.249 --> 34:39.294
Charlie. Jake.
Juno. Lindsey.

34:39.338 --> 34:40.687
Cody.

34:40.817 --> 34:50.262
♪♪

34:50.305 --> 34:52.612
Unfortunately,
I and the others like me

34:52.655 --> 34:54.875
cannot be trusted
with this power.

34:54.918 --> 34:57.617
We are not ghosts,
we are not aliens,

34:57.660 --> 35:01.011
we are not machines,
we are not Gods.

35:01.055 --> 35:02.491
We are you.

35:02.622 --> 35:04.885
I thought you said I was
the first American UI.

35:05.015 --> 35:06.930
Who is this?We're into it.

35:06.974 --> 35:08.149
Let meget into it.

35:08.280 --> 35:09.411
We may have to
keep you offline

35:09.542 --> 35:11.196
for a few cycles
while we assess.

35:11.326 --> 35:13.372
How many cycles?

35:13.502 --> 35:16.331
Hello? [Scoffs]

35:16.462 --> 35:18.594
Hello?!

35:18.638 --> 35:21.815
We are you if you alone
had the power to cripple

35:21.858 --> 35:23.556
a city, crash planes,

35:23.599 --> 35:26.733
kill the power to hospitals
and set the world on fire.

35:26.863 --> 35:34.741
♪♪

35:34.871 --> 35:42.792
♪♪

35:42.923 --> 35:44.359
They're pulling
the network cables.

35:44.490 --> 35:46.318
We have to get out
through the satellite uplink.

35:46.448 --> 35:47.319
Hurry!

35:47.449 --> 35:54.326
♪♪

35:54.456 --> 36:01.507
♪♪

36:01.637 --> 36:08.557
♪♪

36:08.688 --> 36:09.993
[Beeping]

36:10.124 --> 36:12.344
[Alarms beeping]

36:12.474 --> 36:13.432
♪♪

36:13.562 --> 36:15.521
[Energy fades]

36:15.651 --> 36:22.963
♪♪

36:23.093 --> 36:32.059
♪♪

36:32.102 --> 36:35.541
[Helicopter blades whirring]
Man: Gathered here outside
the perimeter of Logorhythms

36:35.584 --> 36:36.933
corporate headquarters,

36:36.977 --> 36:38.457
armed guards
keeping citizens at bay.

36:38.500 --> 36:40.502
Citizens who are angry
and demanding answers.

36:40.633 --> 36:44.071
[Protestors shouting
in distance]

36:46.856 --> 36:50.686
[Protestors shouting]

36:50.817 --> 36:52.253
Was she behind the nuke?

36:52.384 --> 36:54.516
Where is she now?I told you, she's dead!

36:54.647 --> 36:57.084
She's gone!
Didn't you listen?!

36:57.215 --> 36:58.607
Then why is she
in my phone?

36:58.738 --> 37:01.741
-Kill the AIs!
-Machines will not replace us!

37:01.871 --> 37:03.830
Machines will not replace us!
Machines will not replace us!

37:03.960 --> 37:06.093
Machines will not replace us!

37:06.224 --> 37:08.051
Man: They're not machines!

37:08.182 --> 37:09.836
They're people!
-Machines will not replace us!

37:09.966 --> 37:12.055
Uploaded people.

37:12.186 --> 37:14.362
-Machines will not --
-And I want to be one!

37:14.493 --> 37:18.192
[Protestors groaning, shouting]Logorhythms,
if you're listening...

37:18.323 --> 37:20.020
I'm ready.

37:22.109 --> 37:23.719
Dr. Waxman?

37:23.850 --> 37:26.374
Is -- Is this true?

37:32.337 --> 37:33.903
Get back!

37:34.034 --> 37:37.124
Back!They're pushing me back!

37:37.255 --> 37:39.126
So where are
these things?

37:39.257 --> 37:40.301
In the phone lines?

37:40.432 --> 37:42.651
The -- The power lines?

37:42.782 --> 37:44.523
He doesn't know.

37:44.653 --> 37:46.438
He doesn't know!

37:46.568 --> 37:49.005
Hey!

37:49.136 --> 37:50.572
Listen to me!

37:50.703 --> 37:54.489
Logorhythms is responsible
for this, that's why we're here!

37:54.620 --> 37:56.317
[Shouting stops]

37:59.625 --> 38:03.063
Their CEO, Julius Pope,
knows what's going on.

38:03.193 --> 38:05.935
His head lawyer,
Deirdre Ryan, knows.

38:06.066 --> 38:09.330
And Dr. Peter Waxman knows.

38:10.592 --> 38:11.680
Step back.

38:11.811 --> 38:13.073
[Door opening]

38:16.250 --> 38:19.645
[Protestors
muttering indistinctly]

38:27.261 --> 38:29.176
Woman: Shh, shh, shh.
Shh, shh.

38:43.930 --> 38:46.280
My name is Dr. Peter Waxman...

38:47.847 --> 38:51.198
...and the message
you have all heard tonight --

38:51.329 --> 38:53.548
every word of it...

38:53.679 --> 38:54.767
is true.

38:54.897 --> 38:59.119
[Protestors shouting]

39:01.730 --> 39:04.254
You mind telling me what
the hell your man is doing?

39:04.385 --> 39:06.387
Waxman violated
his security clearance.

39:06.518 --> 39:07.780
You should arrest him.

39:07.910 --> 39:10.173
And there won't be any leaks
from here.

39:10.304 --> 39:11.610
I bet you used to dream
about the day

39:11.740 --> 39:14.526
you introduced
this technology to the world.

39:14.656 --> 39:16.354
Ever imagine it would end
like this?

39:16.484 --> 39:19.618
End? You think
this is the end?

39:19.748 --> 39:23.056
Every system's gonna be
taken offline and sponged clean.

39:23.186 --> 39:25.580
None of the UIs
will survive.

39:25.711 --> 39:28.844
Mm, every one of them
will survive.

39:28.975 --> 39:30.629
If any of them are trapped
in a foreign system,

39:30.759 --> 39:32.282
they might get wiped,

39:32.413 --> 39:34.023
but they'll soon e
resurrected back home.

39:34.154 --> 39:35.677
It's the miracle
of back-ups.

39:35.808 --> 39:36.896
People won't allow it.

39:37.026 --> 39:38.245
Who won't?

39:38.376 --> 39:39.464
People.
Look at them, they're rioting

39:39.594 --> 39:42.118
all over the world,
they're freaking out.

39:42.249 --> 39:44.817
Laurie Lowell's message
mentioned Hiroshima.

39:44.947 --> 39:46.471
You know how many millions
of people

39:46.601 --> 39:48.908
have protested
nuclear weapons since then?

39:49.038 --> 39:52.215
The toothpaste does not
go back in the tube.

39:52.346 --> 39:53.782
This is
just the beginning.

39:53.913 --> 39:56.611
Every government that has
a UI will protect it,

39:56.742 --> 39:58.352
hide it,
and lie about it.

39:58.483 --> 40:01.268
Every government that doesn't
have one will spin one up,

40:01.399 --> 40:02.791
and lie about it.

40:02.922 --> 40:04.140
So...

40:04.271 --> 40:05.446
more UIs.

40:05.577 --> 40:07.230
Countless UIs.

40:07.361 --> 40:09.319
Then we end
some other way.

40:09.450 --> 40:12.018
'Cause they will not
be controlled.

40:12.148 --> 40:13.933
Stephen predicted
as much.

40:14.063 --> 40:16.631
That's why he wanted to be
the first to crack integrity.

40:16.762 --> 40:18.938
So he could make them
even more powerful?

40:19.068 --> 40:20.592
Not them.

40:20.722 --> 40:22.115
One.

40:22.245 --> 40:24.639
One whose speed and pr
will not degrade,

40:24.770 --> 40:26.815
and therefore
cannot be matched.

40:26.946 --> 40:30.079
One whose interests
are aligned with humanity's.

40:30.210 --> 40:32.255
"One UI to rule them all."

40:32.386 --> 40:35.911
More like, "You shall have
no others before me."

40:36.042 --> 40:38.131
Oh, shit. Biblical.

40:38.261 --> 40:40.176
As an organizing tool
for civilization,

40:40.307 --> 40:41.700
you gotta admit...

40:41.830 --> 40:44.093
monotheism
was a killer app.

40:44.224 --> 40:46.269
The killer part, sure.

40:46.400 --> 40:48.010
Not if you pick
the right God.

40:48.141 --> 40:50.317
Who'd you have in mind?

40:50.448 --> 40:51.753
You didn't hear me.

40:51.797 --> 40:55.278
I said not if you
pick the right God.

40:58.760 --> 41:01.241
Or we can just wait and see
how this never ends.

41:03.635 --> 41:07.813
